s Festschrift. In addition to introductory essays which provide personal and intellectual histories of Anthony Reid the man, there is a range of original scholarly contributions addressing historical issues which Reid has researched during his career. Divided into sections which examine Southeast Asia in the world, early modern Southeast Asia, and modern Southeast Asia, these works engage with issues ranging from the Age of Commerce and comparative Eurasian history, to nationalism, ethnic hybridity, Islam, technological change, and the Chinese and Arabs in Southeast Asia. The authors include some of the foremost historians of Southeast Asia in our generation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh1 aAndaya, Barbara Watson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndaya, Leonard Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCribb, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElson, R.E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGungwu, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunko, Koizumi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKathirithamby-Wells, Jeyamalar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumar, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLieberman, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLombard, Denys, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManguin, Pierre-Yves, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTana, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTana, Li, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWade